## SMS Modularity (Strategy Pattern)

The SMS service is fully modular — providers can be swapped without affecting any consumer.

### Architecture

```
Contracts/SmsProviderInterface.php    ← Interface (send, name)
Providers/DhiraaguSmsProvider.php     ← Concrete implementation
Services/SmsService.php               ← Orchestrator (accepts interface via DI)
DTOs/SmsMessage.php                   ← Input DTO (to, message, type)
```

### How It Works

```php
// SmsProviderInterface — implement this for new providers
interface SmsProviderInterface {
    public function send(string $phone, string $message): array;
    public function name(): string;
}

// DI binding in AppServiceProvider
$this->app->bind(SmsProviderInterface::class, DhiraaguSmsProvider::class);

// All consumers use SmsService (never the provider directly)
$smsService = app(SmsService::class);
$log = $smsService->send(new SmsMessage(to: $phone, message: $msg, type: 'otp'));
```

### Swapping SMS Provider

1. Create new provider: `app/Domains/Notifications/Providers/TwilioSmsProvider.php`
2. Implement `SmsProviderInterface`
3. Change one line in `AppServiceProvider`: `$this->app->bind(SmsProviderInterface::class, TwilioSmsProvider::class);`
4. No other code changes needed

### Consumers (3 total)

- `CustomerPortalController` — OTP codes
- `ReceiptPageController` — Receipt delivery via SMS
- `SmsPromotionController` — Bulk promotional SMS

