## Frontend Architecture

### Admin Dashboard (`apps/admin-dashboard/`)

```
src/
├── api.ts              # ~77 API functions using apiFetch()
├── App.tsx             # Router + PermissionGuard wrappers
├── main.tsx            # Entry point
├── index.css           # Global styles
├── components/
│   ├── Layout.tsx      # Sidebar nav (permission-filtered) + top bar
│   ├── SharedUI.tsx    # PageHeader, StatCard primitives
│   ├── ErrorBoundary.tsx
│   └── ui/             # Badge, Button, Card, Modal, Input, Tabs, Toast, Toggle, Skeleton, EmptyState
├── hooks/
│   ├── usePageTitle.ts
│   └── usePermissions.ts   # Fetches effective perms, provides can(slug)
└── pages/              # 22 page components (one file per page)
```

### Coding Conventions (Admin Dashboard)

1. **One file per page** — All state, handlers, and JSX in a single `.tsx` file in `pages/`
2. **API calls** — All through `api.ts` using `apiFetch()`. Never call fetch directly in pages.
3. **Styling** — Inline styles via JS objects. No CSS modules, no Tailwind (except SettingsPage legacy).
4. **State** — React `useState` + `useEffect`. No Redux/Zustand.
5. **UI components** — Import from `components/ui/` (Button, Card, Modal, Badge, Input, Tabs, Toast, Toggle, Skeleton, EmptyState)
6. **Shared components** — Import from `SharedUI.tsx` (PageHeader, StatCard)
7. **Page title** — Call `usePageTitle('Page Name')` at top of component
8. **Permissions** — Use `usePermissions()` hook; check with `can('permission.slug')`
9. **Dates** — Use `Intl.DateTimeFormat` (no moment/dayjs/date-fns)
10. **Icons** — Import from `lucide-react`
11. **No emojis** in code unless user requests

### New Page Template

```tsx
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { usePageTitle } from '../hooks/usePageTitle';
import { PageHeader } from '../components/SharedUI';
import { Card } from '../components/ui/Card';
import { Button } from '../components/ui/Button';
import { fetchGiftCards, createGiftCard } from '../api';

export default function GiftCardsPage() {
  usePageTitle('Gift Cards');
  const [cards, setCards] = useState<any[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchGiftCards().then(data => {
      setCards(data.data);
      setLoading(false);
    });
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      <PageHeader title="Gift Cards" />
      {/* Table, modals, etc. */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Then: add route in `App.tsx` with `<PermissionGuard>`, add nav item in `Layout.tsx` with `permission` field.

